    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-18T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.51/2953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1942-04-18T15:00:00+03:00">April 18, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 18—1:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>318. Reference Embassy’s 316, April 15.<note n="72" xml:id="d373fn72">Not
                        printed; this telegram reported that the loan was announced on April 14, in
                        the amount of 10 billion rubles for a term of 20 years (861.51/2950).</note>
                    The Soviet press of April 17 publishes an announcement that the 1942 National
                    Defense Loan was over-subscribed within 2 days. Former loans have usually
                    required from 1 to 4 weeks until fully subscribed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
